    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nIt's not possible to have the Nvim server exit automatically when an client attached to a non-stdio channel crashes or is killed. This leads to a dangling server, which may be undesired in cases like after `:restart` on a server that was previously embedded. As can be seen in the `:restart` tests, after `:restart` killing the TUI won't stop the restarted server, so the server needs to be quit manually.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nA client on non-stdio channel can become an \"owner\" of an Nvim server, so that the server exits automatically when the channels is closed.\n\nA possible solution is to add an \"owner\" flag to `nvim_ui_attach`. However:\n- It's not clear how the server should be behave when multiple UI set the \"owner\" flag.\n- This doesn't allow a non-UI client to become an \"owner\".",
